child.pub-comments: Child of West (Bird's head), Ruhlen 1987. Comrie says: This is listed by Wurm (206) as a West Bird's Head language, but with a question mark. It is also listed in the 13th edition of ethnologue (from 1996) as Kuwani [xku], with an entry ending "Uncomfirmed. Survey needed." It isn't listed in later editions of Ethnologue. I have consulted with a linguist who knows the area (Ger Reesink, Leiden U), and he confirms that there is no evidence for such a language - it is not, for instance, listed by Voorhoeve (op. cit.)
